        "Tafseer": "1. Analysis of Words and Explanation of Verses\n\nHa, Meem. The revelation of the Book is from Allah, the Exalted in Might, the Wise. (1-2)\n\nThe Qur'anic name of this Surah is also 'Ha-Meem'. We have pointed out in the commentary of the preceding Surahs that the sharing of names among the Surahs is proof of the sharing of their contents. Thus, if you reflect, it emerges that there is a highly clear common denominator between the two Surahs. Consequently, the subsequent discussions will bring their shared theme to the forefront, and also reveal the summary of all 'Ha-Meem' Surahs which have passed before."
