    {
        "SurahNumber": 46,
        "AyahNumber": 25,
        "Tafseer": "\"Destroying everything by command of its Lord. And they became so that nothing was seen except their dwellings. Thus do We recompense the criminal people.\" (25)\n\nThis points to the destruction of that wind—showing that it destroyed everything to the extent that nothing remained except the traces of their houses.\n\n'Thus do We recompense the criminal people'—meaning do not think that this is merely a story of the past; We punish the criminals in this very way. If the Quraysh adopt the same way 'Aad adopted, there is no reason why His dealing with them is different. They will necessarily face the same end. His law is the same for everyone."
