    {
        "SurahNumber": 46,
        "AyahNumber": 26,
        "Tafseer": "\"And We had certainly established them in such as We have not established you, and We made for them hearing and vision and hearts. But their hearing and vision and hearts availed them not at all when they used to reject the signs of Allah, and they were enveloped by what they used to mock.\" (26)\n\nWarning to the Quraysh\n\nThis addresses the Quraysh to show the lesson: the abundance of resources, power, and glory which We bestowed upon them has not been bestowed upon you, but see, when We willed to seize them, they could not save themselves! We gave them the capabilities of hearing, sight, and heart, but since they were not ready to accept the light of Our signs, their hearing, sight, and hearts were of no use, but they were caught in that punishment which they mocked.\n\nThe Capabilities of Hearing, Sight, and Heart are Enlightened by the Signs of Allah\n\nFrom this, the reality is clarified: the true light in hearing, sight, and the heart is produced by the signs of Allah. If they are not enlightened by the light of His signs, their reach is limited only to physical sensations, and on these physical sensations they spend all their energy to achieve physical benefits. The consequence of this physicalism is that these capabilities become blunt. They can neither reflect on any other aspect of things nor feel any need to do so, whereas the primary aspect to reflect upon is that. For this reason, regarding such people, the Qur'an stated: they have ears but they do not hear, they have eyes but they do not see, they have hearts but they do not understand."
