    {
        "SurahNumber": 46,
        "AyahNumber": 28,
        "Tafseer": "\"Then why did those not support them whom they had taken besides Allah as partners [and] gods to bring [them] near [to Him]? Rather, they departed from them. And that was their falsehood and what they had been inventing.\" (28)\n\nA Question\n\nThis is a question to the Quraysh—asking: if your assumption is that your deities will save you, why did their deities not save them from His punishment, when they had also taken them as a means of proximity to God? 'Rather, they departed from them'—meaning they vanished at the very first moment, and no one came to help.\n\n'And that was their falsehood and what they had been inventing'—meaning it was proven that this was entirely their lie and fabrication; they made them deities according to their own assumption, and fabricated the lie against God that they are His beloved ones and He has associated them.\n\n'To bring [them] near' (qurbanan) is the object of cause (maf'ul lahu). This points to that belief of the polytheists which has been mentioned in their statement: 'We only worship them that they may bring us nearer to Allah in position.'\n\nIt should be kept in mind: the polytheists did not worship their deities as creators of things, but as those who are beloved of God, whose worship is a means of proximity. The belief regarding the angels has been discussed."
