    {
        "SurahNumber": 46,
        "AyahNumber": 33,
        "Tafseer": "\"Do they not see that Allah, who created the heavens and the earth and did not weary of their creation, is competent to give life to the dead? Yes. Indeed, He is over all things competent.\" (33)\n\nWarning the Deniers\n\nThis is a warning to the deniers at the end of the Surah—stating: have they not reflected on the fact that the God Who created the heavens and the earth, and faced no difficulty in this, is competent to raise the dead alive. Exactly this same question has been presented by the Qur'an before the deniers of the Resurrection in other places. For example, He asked: 'Were We then weary with the first creation?' (Qaf: 15). In some places, He asked: is it more difficult to create the heavens and the earth, or to recreate the dead?\n\n'Yes. Indeed, He is over all things competent'—having asked the question, He answered it Himself: 'Yes, Allah Almighty, Who faced no difficulty in creating the heavens and the earth, is not only competent to raise the dead alive, but is competent over everything.' We have been pointing in various places to this style of expression of the Qur'an—showing that when there is no room for the addressee to escape from an answer, the Qur'an presents that answer before him."
