    {
        "SurahNumber": 46,
        "AyahNumber": 34,
        "Tafseer": "\"And the Day those who disbelieved are exposed to the Fire [it will be said], 'Is this not the truth?' They will say, 'Yes, by our Lord.' He will say, 'Then taste the punishment because you used to disbelieve.'\" (34)\n\nThis is a depiction of that warning—showing: keep always present that Day when the disbelievers will be presented before the Fire and asked: 'Tell us, has the Resurrection proven to be a reality or not?' At that time, they will reply, swearing by their Lord: 'Yes! By our Lord, it has indeed proven to be a real event!' Following this admission of theirs, the command will be: 'Now go, taste the punishment as a retribution for your disbelief!' It should be kept in mind that the proofs of the Resurrection in the horizons and ourselves are so clear that no wise person can deny them. Whosoever denied the Resurrection did so not because of any proof, but purely because they were not ready to sacrifice the desires of the self. Obviously, those who denied their own intellect, their nature, and all the prophets and messengers in following their desires deserve no leniency."
