    {
        "SurahNumber": 46,
        "AyahNumber": 35,
        "Tafseer": "\"So be patient, [O Muhammad], as were patient those of determination among the messengers and do not be impatient for them. It will be - on the Day they see that which they are promised - as though they had not remained [in the world] except an hour of a day. [This is] notification. And will [any] be destroyed except the defiantly disobedient people?\" (35)\n\nInstruction of Steadfastness to the Prophet\n\nAt the end, this is instruction of patience and steadfastness to the Prophet (pbuh)—stating: just as those of determination among Our messengers faced all oppositions with resolve and remained firm on their stance, you also remain firm on your stance, regardless of all conspiracies and offenses of your enemies.\n\nIn 'among the messengers' (min al-rusul), 'min' is, in my view, for explanation, not for part. All messengers of Allah faced trials, and all achieved success in these trials.\n\n'and do not be impatient for them'—meaning if these people are hastening for the punishment to harass you, do not be impatient for them. The respite which appears long to them today, when the punishment comes, they will feel as if they had remained in the world only for an hour of a day.\n\n'[This is] notification. And will [any] be destroyed except the defiantly disobedient people?'—'notification' (balagh) is the predicate of an omitted subject. To focus all attention on the predicate, the subject is omitted. The meaning is: your duty is only to deliver this warning to them clearly, so that no excuse remains for anyone. After this, if these people are destroyed, they will carry the responsibility. If these foolish people are hastening for the punishment, let them; when it comes, its lightning will fall upon these rebellious people alone!\n\nBy the grace and guidance of the Generous and Caring Lord, the commentary of this Surah is completed on these lines. Praise be to Allah for His favor.\n\nRahman Abad\n4 August, 1976 AD\n7 Shaban, 1396 AH."
